3. LICENSE AUTHENTICATION & VALIDATION
   
   a) REQUIRED AUTHENTICATION
      Pro and Enterprise editions require valid license authentication to
      unlock tier-specific features and capabilities. License validation
      is performed by cryptographic verification of signed license tokens.
   
   b) LICENSE VALIDITY
      A valid license must:
      - Contain an authentic signature from 3D Tech Solutions LLC
      - Not be expired, revoked, or suspended
      - Match the licensed tier and authorized use case
      - Not have been tampered with or modified in any way
   
   c) VOIDING THE LICENSE
      The license is immediately void and unenforceable if:
      - The licensee attempts to circumvent, bypass, or disable the license
        authentication and validation mechanisms
      - The licensee attempts to forge, duplicate, or create unauthorized
        copies of the license token
      - The licensee attempts to modify the license file, its contents, or
        cryptographic signatures
      - The licensee uses the software with an invalid, expired, or revoked
        license
      - The licensee attempts to reverse engineer or analyze the license
        validation code for the purpose of circumvention
      - Any other breach of the license terms occurs
   
   d) CONSEQUENCES OF VOIDING
      Upon license voiding:
      - All rights to use Pro and Enterprise features are immediately
        terminated
      - The licensee must cease all use of the software within 30 days
      - No refunds or credits will be issued
      - 3D Tech Solutions LLC may pursue legal remedies and damages
      - The licensee may be excluded from future beta testing programs
        and commercial licensing

