================================================================================
PART 3: DETERMINING YOUR EDITION
================================================================================

Your Code Scalpel edition is determined by:
- The presence and validity of a signed license file
- The "tier" field in a valid license token
- The absence of a license file indicates Community Edition

Community Edition Features:
- Limited to basic functionality as defined in the documentation
- Available under the MIT License (Part 1)
- No license authentication required

Pro Edition Features:
- Enhanced analysis capabilities (expanded depth limits, file limits, etc.)
- Priority support during beta period
- Requires valid signed license token with tier="pro"

Enterprise Edition Features:
- Unlimited analysis capabilities
- Advanced security analysis and cross-file taint tracking
- Custom metrics and compliance reporting
- Requires valid signed license token with tier="enterprise"

